<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Two-Factor Authentication Enabled</title>
</head>
<body style="margin: 0; padding: 0; font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; background-color: #f4f4f4;">
  <table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="background-color: #f4f4f4; padding: 20px;">
    <tr>
      <td align="center">
        <table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="background-color: #ffffff; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
          <!-- Header -->
          <tr>
            <td style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #28a745 0%, #20c997 100%); padding: 40px 30px; text-align: center;">
              <h1 style="color: #ffffff; margin: 0; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600;">ðŸ”’ 2FA Enabled Successfully</h1>
            </td>
          </tr>

          <!-- Content -->
          <tr>
            <td style="padding: 40px 30px;">
              <h2 style="color: #333333; margin: 0 0 20px; font-size: 24px;">Hello {{firstName}}!</h2>

              <div style="background-color: #d4edda; border-left: 4px solid #28a745; padding: 20px; margin: 0 0 30px;">
                <p style="color: #155724; margin: 0; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: 600;">
                  Two-factor authentication has been successfully enabled on your account.
                </p>
              </div>

              <p style="color: #666666; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 20px; font-size: 16px;">
                Your account is now more secure! From now on, you'll need to provide both your password and a verification code from your authenticator app when logging in.
              </p>

              <h3 style="color: #333333; margin: 0 0 15px; font-size: 18px;">What this means:</h3>

              <ul style="color: #666666; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 30px; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 16px;">
                <li>Enhanced security for your account</li>
                <li>Protection against unauthorized access</li>
                <li>Required authenticator app for login</li>
                <li>Backup codes for emergency access</li>
              </ul>

              <div style="background-color: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 6px; padding: 20px; margin: 0 0 30px;">
                <h4 style="color: #333333; margin: 0 0 15px; font-size: 16px;">Important Information:</h4>
                <table width="100%" cellpadding="8" cellspacing="0">
                  <tr>
                    <td style="color: #666666; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; width: 140px;">Enabled On:</td>
                    <td style="color: #333333; font-size: 14px;">{{enabledAt}}</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td style="color: #666666; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600;">Device:</td>
                    <td style="color: #333333; font-size: 14px;">{{device}}</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td style="color: #666666; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600;">IP Address:</td>
                    <td style="color: #333333; font-size: 14px;">{{ipAddress}}</td>
                  </tr>
                </table>
              </div>

              <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #ffc107; padding: 15px; margin: 0 0 30px;">
                <p style="color: #856404; margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: 600;">
                  Save Your Backup Codes
                </p>
                <p style="color: #856404; margin: 0; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6;">
                  Make sure you've saved your backup codes in a secure location. You'll need them if you lose access to your authenticator app.
                </p>
              </div>

              <h3 style="color: #333333; margin: 0 0 15px; font-size: 18px;">Next time you log in:</h3>

              <ol style="color: #666666; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 30px; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 16px;">
                <li>Enter your email and password as usual</li>
                <li>Open your authenticator app (Google Authenticator, Authy, etc.)</li>
                <li>Enter the 6-digit code shown in the app</li>
                <li>You're in!</li>
              </ol>

              <div style="background-color: #f8d7da; border-left: 4px solid #dc3545; padding: 15px; margin: 0 0 20px;">
                <p style="color: #721c24; margin: 0; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6;">
                  <strong>Didn't enable 2FA?</strong> If you didn't enable two-factor authentication, please contact support immediately at support@aijobportal.com
                </p>
              </div>

              <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                <tr>
                  <td style="background-color: #f8f9fa; border: 2px solid #667eea; border-radius: 6px; text-align: center;">
                    <a href="{{securitySettingsUrl}}" style="display: inline-block; padding: 12px 30px; color: #667eea; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 14px;">
                      View Security Settings
                    </a>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              </table>
            </td>
          </tr>

          <!-- Footer -->
          <tr>
            <td style="background-color: #f8f9fa; padding: 30px; text-align: center; border-top: 1px solid #e9ecef;">
              <p style="color: #999999; margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 14px;">
                Â© 2025 AI Job Portal. All rights reserved.
              </p>
              <p style="color: #999999; margin: 0; font-size: 12px;">
                This is an automated security notification.
              </p>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</body>
</html>
